  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that development of symptoms characteristic of Clostridium
      difficile infection will be 2-3 times higher in asymptomatic carriers, compared to that of
      non carriers and expect to find risk factors for development of symptomatic clostridium
      difficile.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
